<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-76-0497 </DOCNO><TEXT>Computed tomography (CT) and histologic data were compared for 60 casesof hepatic lymphoma (44 non-Hodgkin's lymphomas, 16 Hodgkin's disease).CT scans obtained after intravenous injection of contrast material hada sensitivity of 80% and a specificity of 94%. Radiologic patterns, seeneither in combination or alone, included: hypodense multinodular pattern(46 cases), hepatomegaly (19 cases), normal appearance (12 cases) andsolitary tumor (4 cases). Splenic involvement was noted in 31 cases.24 refs.; 6 figs.</TEXT></DOC>